        "text": "fast.\"",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " The cedar genus belonging to the order Coniferae, is odoriferous, very lasting, and without knots. The numerous good qualities which it possesses are spoken to in the variety of uses, and good kind of uses, to which it was put - these all crowned by the almost solitary spiritualized appropriation of the tree, found in ",
        "children": []
