        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 2:3, 8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and some other passages, we may be led to believe that the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "cedar",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " as the name of timber was used occasionally very generically. Nevertheless, the very passages in question instance by name the other specific kinds of wood. Two of the chief kinds of cedar were the Lebanon and the Deodara, which is said not to have grown in Syria, but abounds in the Himalayas. And as the use of the Lebanon cedar for some ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
