        "text": "masts",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " of ships) is almost out of the question, it is exceedingly probable that this ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "Deodars",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " and some other varieties of pines are comprehended under the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "eh-rez.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " Dean Stanley points out what may be described as very interesting moral ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "landmark",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " uses of the celebrated cedars of Lebanon, in those passages which speak of Solomon's sweep of knowledge, commencing in the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "dewing",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
